# Keep scripts LF. sbatch itself tolerates CRLF (our CRLF scripts ran fine on the
# cluster), but `bash -n` and running a script directly instead of through sbatch both
# fail on it with "syntax error: unexpected end of file", since "fi\r" is not "fi".
# Pinning to LF keeps them lintable and runnable either way.
*.sh text eol=lf
*.py text eol=lf
